article:
'Holmberg' is primarily a Scandinavian surname formed from the words holm(e)
meaning islet and berg meaning mountain. It is a relatively common name, at
least in Sweden, which has to do with the fact that many Swedish place names
contain the suffixes -holm, -holmen or -berg, -berga, -berget.
